              "text": "## Vector Operations\n\nIn linear algebra, the dot product is a fundamental operation that takes two equal-length sequences of numbers and returns a single scalar. It represents the product of the magnitudes of the two vectors and the cosine of the angle between them.\n\nThe dot product of two vectors $\\mathbf{a}$ and $\\mathbf{b}$ is defined as:\n\n\\[\n\\mathbf{a} \\cdot \\mathbf{b} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} a_i b_i = a_1 b_1 + a_2 b_2 + \\dots + a_n b_n\n\\]\n\nTo produce the equation above in LaTeX, you would use the following code:\n\n```latex\n\\[\n\\mathbf{a} \\cdot \\mathbf{b} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} a_i b_i = a_1 b_1 + a_2 b_2 + \\dots + a_n b_n\n\\]\n```",
